@lguohan / @yakivh 
I guess if PTF aligned with 1.2 headers it should be pushed to [v1.2 branch](https://github.com/opencomputeproject/SAI/tree/v1.2) as well.
How do you think?

You can still use SAI_BUFFER_PROFILE_ATTR_SHARED_DYNAMIC_TH and
SAI_BUFFER_PROFILE_ATTR_SHARED_STATIC_TH

So sample Sonic flow could be 
             else if (fvField(*i) == buffer_dynamic_th_field_name)		              else if (fvField(*i) == buffer_dynamic_th_field_name)
              {		              {
                  attr.id = SAI_BUFFER_PROFILE_ATTR_SHARED_DYNAMIC_TH;		                  attr.id = SAI_BUFFER_PROFILE_ATTR_SHARED_DYNAMIC_TH;
                  attr.value.u32 = (uint32_t)stoul(fvValue(*i));		                  attr.value.u32 = (uint32_t)stoul(fvValue(*i));
                  attribs.push_back(attr);		                  attribs.push_back(attr);
              }
That flow doesn't set the buffer profile mode (since by default it is inherit)

Or you could write this explicitley
             else if (fvField(*i) == buffer_dynamic_th_field_name)		              else if (fvField(*i) == buffer_dynamic_th_field_name)
              {		              {
                 attr.id = SAI_BUFFER_PROFILE_ATTR_THRESHOLD_MODE;		
                 attr.value.s32 = SAI_BUFFER_PROFILE_THRESHOLD_MODE_INHERIT_BUFFER_POOL_MODE;		
                 attribs.push_back(attr);		
 		
                  attr.id = SAI_BUFFER_PROFILE_ATTR_SHARED_DYNAMIC_TH;		                  attr.id = SAI_BUFFER_PROFILE_ATTR_SHARED_DYNAMIC_TH;
                  attr.value.u32 = (uint32_t)stoul(fvValue(*i));		                  attr.value.u32 = (uint32_t)stoul(fvValue(*i));
                  attribs.push_back(attr);		                  attribs.push_back(attr);
              }

